7. Robotics Concepts Visualized

The platform will help students understand complex robotics concepts.

Forward Kinematics

Shows how joint angles determine robot position.

Visualization:

Real-time robot arm movement

Joint rotation animation

Inverse Kinematics

Calculates joint angles required to reach a target position.

Students can move the robot end-effector and observe joint adjustments.

Coordinate Systems

Students learn different coordinate frames:

Base frame

Tool frame

World frame

The system will visualize coordinate axes in 3D.

Path Planning

Students will visualize robot movement paths.

Types of paths:

Linear motion

Circular motion

Joint motion

