17. Conclusion

The development of an AR/VR-based virtual robotics laboratory represents a transformative solution for modern engineering education. By combining immersive technologies with robotics simulation, this platform can bridge the gap between theoretical learning and practical experience.

Students will gain the ability to explore robotics systems in an interactive environment, experiment with robot programming, and understand complex robotic concepts visually.

The platform offers a cost-effective, safe, and scalable alternative to traditional robotics laboratories, making advanced robotics education accessible to institutions worldwide.

As industries increasingly adopt automation and robotics, such virtual learning platforms will play a critical role in preparing the next generation of engineers for the future of intelligent manufacturing.